\ul\b\f0\fs44 Learning and Observations:\par
\ulnone\b0 Learning:\par

2)Arduino board has Digital pins and \cf3\highlight4 Analog pins.\par
Digital pin provides Input as well as Output, but Analog pin provides input only.\par
3)The Arduino board has ~ sign in Digital pin side which is also known as Pulse Width Modulation(PWM).\par
These pins help\rquote s in getting analog results with digital means.\par
\cf2\highlight0 4)How to work with cuircts on breadboard.\par
\cf3\highlight4 5)Since the LED can bear a limited supply of voltage so we have used resistance in series\par

6. Digital Pin provides 5V Power supply to the circuit.\par
\b\fs44 Observations:\par
\b0\fs36 1)when we connect the \lquote n\rquote  terminal of the LED to other terminal except ground(GND), hence the circuit will be worng and we cannot get the desired output.\par
2)I connected the \lquote p\rquote  terminal of the p-n junction diodes to the Digital pins 0 in combination with the resistance, and \lquote n\rquote  terminals with the ground(GND).\par
3)After uploading the code on the Arduino software, the LED\rquote s started blinking in a fixed time interval of 1000miliseconds as given in code.\par
